{"active_answer": "Nawa no Jiba (“The Magnetic Field of Rope”)", "active_index": 258, "active_question": "What is the title of Sugiura Norio's retrospective exhibition?", "audit_index": 2, "decision": "drop", "document_sha256": "9fa6e67dad27cd6ceb5b2e8eed57a4c8a12ec3a85b393d70d33862498c0eb63b", "fact_id": "fact-854eee7f7afdc00ab504", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 258, "baseline_rows": 549, "baseline_sha256": "d2998dcacbe7dbc02ed8ccf6dbbab953fdc431eed3c9845d3051fa9badf4cb23", "prior_context_merit_review": false}, "reason": "The retrospective's proper-name lookup is low-value event trivia; the source's career and photographic-history context is more substantive.", "reason_code": "incidental_exhibition_title_lookup", "review_pass": "first_context_merit_review_of_v47_projection_row", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v48", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 8, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 9, "risk_score": 1, "short_question_points": 1}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v48", "source": "kinbakutoday", "source_document": "data/raw/kinbakutoday_56b268785cbff3bb.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "1bc966947f7a7b1ed4166aecea5cb0a5bd32693f927c987ba7fbc75722f111b2", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "The exhibition, held Feb. 2-7 across two floors in a gallery in Tokyo’s trendy Harajuku district, attracted about 500 visitors, many of whom had contributed to a crowd-funding campaign that made the event possible. Titled Nawa no Jiba (“The Magnetic Field of Rope”), the show presented approximately 100 photographs from throughout Sugiura’s career, ranging from the 1970s to the present.", "support_evidence_sha256": "a700da1f8bd915991b0ff0bf01f47a492235e5669ae45ff30cb2410a9757098f", "url": "https://www.kinbakutoday.com/sugiura-norio-celebrating-45-years-bondage-photography/"}
{"active_answer": "a cuff that will not tighten when we pull on the tail", "active_index": 11, "active_question": "According to Rope365, what is a single column tie?", "audit_index": 3, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "11de0cc10c31ee031dcff94c630c6f2b0ab34f94f800ac6bddd2d28ccbfabefd", "fact_id": "fact-9e1d84a06b0b7efe1dc3", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 11, "baseline_rows": 549, "baseline_sha256": "d2998dcacbe7dbc02ed8ccf6dbbab953fdc431eed3c9845d3051fa9badf4cb23", "prior_context_merit_review": false}, "reason": "The answer defines a foundational structure by its essential behavior under tail tension.", "reason_code": "foundational_non_tightening_column_tie_definition", "review_pass": "first_context_merit_review_of_v47_projection_row", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v48", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 12, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 9, "risk_score": 1, "short_question_points": 1}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v48", "source": "rope365", "source_document": "data/raw/rope365_f250f228cc370052.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "9fd56bab80ef0b62d81f7b8b7d6da4bb90047eafeec4098dc23f9efd042bae23", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "Most ties start with a single column tie, it is the first anchor to the body. A single column tie is a cuff that will not tighten when we pull on the tail. “Column” refers to anything you can tie around: a leg, a torso, a bedpost etc.", "support_evidence_sha256": "7a3a4e1b4569bcbcee6319cdf06cd28f544c4d5ceea43dbd556222863c88f99e", "url": "https://rope365.com/single-column-tie/"}
{"active_answer": "Participating in a first aid class", "active_index": 361, "active_question": "What training does Rope365 recommend for learning emergency incident response?", "audit_index": 4, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "f83771d810b2b197ec3a0fb58660ac529b996951413e58fa87ff48e37f52a6d7", "fact_id": "fact-55f26dc889d7aaa6c515", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 361, "baseline_rows": 549, "baseline_sha256": "d2998dcacbe7dbc02ed8ccf6dbbab953fdc431eed3c9845d3051fa9badf4cb23", "prior_context_merit_review": false}, "reason": "Formal first-aid training is practical preparation for responding to common emergencies rather than improvising during an incident.", "reason_code": "first_aid_emergency_preparation", "review_pass": "first_context_merit_review_of_v47_projection_row", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v48", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 6, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 10, "risk_score": 0, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v48", "source": "rope365", "source_document": "data/raw/rope_resources_v1/rope365__7b5d548036392d65fec7.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "52bd91ac138ed002c3c46ccde4233dc586c1f59297e77ff254cefeda6f779018", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "The best way to be prepared for an incident is to visualize what you are about to do and figure out what could go wrong. For example, what would happen if you or your partner faints? What would you do if one of your hands got injured? Participating in a first aid class is a good way to get training for emergency incident response and will cover many common injuries.", "support_evidence_sha256": "d7d7ecfdccec41850185ed6d8f625abccb22a1881c467db0a43e467f1590b4ce", "url": "https://rope365.com/safety/"}
{"active_answer": "Where ropes can and can’t go on the body", "active_index": 322, "active_question": "What should partners agree about rope placement before a scene?", "audit_index": 5, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "b316fd1a708dcb7688d44826496dd58b8c06d20b9c01d8daa73e99e7704abc53", "fact_id": "fact-9fb9d97a8ac45f31a092", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 322, "baseline_rows": 549, "baseline_sha256": "d2998dcacbe7dbc02ed8ccf6dbbab953fdc431eed3c9845d3051fa9badf4cb23", "prior_context_merit_review": false}, "reason": "Agreeing where rope may touch is concrete informed-consent guidance, especially when hygiene and intimate areas are relevant.", "reason_code": "pre_scene_rope_placement_agreement", "review_pass": "first_context_merit_review_of_v47_projection_row", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v48", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 9, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 10, "risk_score": 0, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v48", "source": "anatomiestudio", "source_document": "data/raw/anatomiestudio_144932682af9c846.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "3e77a59322805eb277e5cc7e86fb5592e71b889b3c95197c2c401d2533d2c1c8", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "- Where ropes can and can’t go on the body during a scene", "support_evidence_sha256": "c6fecd44961b7b3bd0c623ff5866993dff3698832ec9e0823fcaf202deaeb732", "url": "https://www.anatomiestudio.com/blog/cleaning-jute-rope-after-sexy-time"}
{"active_answer": "either twisted rope or a solid braid with no core", "active_index": 447, "active_question": "Which coreless rope constructions does Crash Restraint recommend for bondage?", "audit_index": 6, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "de26f9c29b9dacf39ed1901dd367462c12e3569c38baf5e8e4d6861782dedced", "fact_id": "fact-166c469beb2e54bb5e96", "paraphrase_rationale": "The answer removes the parenthetical strand-count aside while preserving the source's two recommended coreless construction categories.", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 447, "baseline_rows": 549, "baseline_sha256": "d2998dcacbe7dbc02ed8ccf6dbbab953fdc431eed3c9845d3051fa9badf4cb23", "prior_context_merit_review": false}, "reason": "The answer preserves a construction-level equipment recommendation and explicitly excludes a core from the braided option.", "reason_code": "protected_coreless_bondage_rope_construction", "review_pass": "first_context_merit_review_of_v47_projection_row", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v48", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 10, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 10, "risk_score": 0, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v48", "source": "crash_restraint", "source_document": "data/rope_resource_manual_v1.jsonl", "source_document_file_sha256": "caee3a972ee70f6e8f23cd3de561bc673c54705e64df58cfc0c867e75995c3bc", "source_support": "manual_paraphrase", "support_evidence": "Rope for bondage should be either twisted (most commonly with 3, but sometimes 4, strands), or a solid braid with no core.", "support_evidence_sha256": "de26f9c29b9dacf39ed1901dd367462c12e3569c38baf5e8e4d6861782dedced", "url": "https://crash-restraint.com/ties/3"}
{"active_answer": "Not to be touched, slapped, spanked, groped, played with or otherwise molested without consent", "active_index": 320, "active_question": "What should newcomers to kink events expect regarding physical contact?", "audit_index": 7, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "03bb1af918ad3ed44208dc4805e48e40718f47d3ffc8994d47a54035e70140d2", "fact_id": "fact-ee87d53a840fc422951b", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 320, "baseline_rows": 549, "baseline_sha256": "d2998dcacbe7dbc02ed8ccf6dbbab953fdc431eed3c9845d3051fa9badf4cb23", "prior_context_merit_review": false}, "reason": "The source clearly states that attending a kink event does not imply consent to physical or sexualized contact.", "reason_code": "newcomer_event_contact_consent", "review_pass": "first_context_merit_review_of_v47_projection_row", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v48", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 14, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 10, "risk_score": 0, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v48", "source": "wykd", "source_document": "data/raw/wykd_944e4e6d621a97c9.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "5d495bf93380ad381f23068c4e51ffab4d519822f32c9db8f33aa07d1d8d2add", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "- Not to be touched, slapped, spanked, groped, played with or otherwise molested without consent", "support_evidence_sha256": "2a95a0d573ac5288ef02efe3d517663e73c8f26539ba50f84a1a841a4bf359f4", "url": "https://wykd.com/learning/2012/11/03/newness-and-getting-out-into-the-kink-community/"}
{"active_answer": "the quality of seeing another in a profound and real way and taking an action that is neither necessary nor requested, in order to recognize them", "active_index": 84, "active_question": "How does the author of ‘Rope and Kindness’ define kindness?", "audit_index": 8, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "206ae74a1ff41b679a5901e25230bbb225cb66bc479b796c5895e6f40ee6582d", "fact_id": "fact-38ec1728983f826643a2", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 84, "baseline_rows": 549, "baseline_sha256": "d2998dcacbe7dbc02ed8ccf6dbbab953fdc431eed3c9845d3051fa9badf4cb23", "prior_context_merit_review": false}, "reason": "The question explicitly attributes a coherent relational definition and supports the same article's partner-centered rope ethic retained in v47.", "reason_code": "explicitly_attributed_kindness_definition", "review_pass": "first_context_merit_review_of_v47_projection_row", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v48", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 26, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 10, "risk_score": 0, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v48", "source": "kinbakutoday", "source_document": "data/raw/kinbakutoday_73b16e835ab63cc2.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "bd8302205309d9a82c61d014a83c463cdb4ae7c4772de3b194b21e3a9841a6d4", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "As I see it, kindness is nothing more than the quality of seeing another in a profound and real way and taking an action that is neither necessary nor requested, in order to recognize them. It may be as small as a kind word or as dramatic as buying them a horse (OK, admittedly an outdated gesture). But the essence of kindness is taking the time to see who a person is and what a person needs, perhaps even when they can’t see it themselves, and giving them something special and deliberate in a way which enriches both people’s lives. That has always been the goal I strive for when I tie.", "support_evidence_sha256": "93ec10f99e6fa2b0e9db7e0861702198439cb58c5ab75c1b88ee6f3551aa0771", "url": "https://www.kinbakutoday.com/rope-and-kindness/"}
{"active_answer": "Clean up your play space", "active_index": 73, "active_question": "How does Rope365 recommend reducing tripping hazards in the rope-play space?", "audit_index": 9, "decision": "keep", "document_sha256": "f83771d810b2b197ec3a0fb58660ac529b996951413e58fa87ff48e37f52a6d7", "fact_id": "fact-52aaf228bd4fb0739e29", "projection_lineage": {"active_index": 73, "baseline_rows": 549, "baseline_sha256": "d2998dcacbe7dbc02ed8ccf6dbbab953fdc431eed3c9845d3051fa9badf4cb23", "prior_context_merit_review": false}, "reason": "Removing mats, rope bags, people, and clutter from the path is direct fall-prevention guidance.", "reason_code": "practical_play_space_trip_prevention", "review_pass": "first_context_merit_review_of_v47_projection_row", "reviewed_at": "2026-07-14", "reviewer": "codex-context-merit-audit-v48", "risk_features": {"answer_tokens": 5, "bare_answer_points": 0, "named_person_trivia_points": 0, "pronoun_count": 0, "question_tokens": 11, "risk_score": 0, "short_question_points": 0}, "schema": "context-merit-audit-v48", "source": "rope365", "source_document": "data/raw/rope_resources_v1/rope365__7b5d548036392d65fec7.json", "source_document_file_sha256": "52bd91ac138ed002c3c46ccde4233dc586c1f59297e77ff254cefeda6f779018", "source_support": "normalized_extractive", "support_evidence": "- Clean up your play space to prevent tripping hazards (mats, rope bag, other people, clutter, etc.),", "support_evidence_sha256": "af1c39535e7cc6e7f5a582829baa4c5a7d95ee3f07b5d31dfd585f7ea04fe145", "url": "https://rope365.com/safety/"}
